						<summary>

						<p>The inscription has the introduction <hi rend="italic">Tirumagaḷ pōla</hi> etc. It records a gift of sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple by Tāḷi Nakkaṉ Ōraḷi, a resident of the village and a nother gift for burning a twilight lamp before god Gaṇapati, by a shepherd.</p>						

